	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1" facs="R 87-11 17 (38)"/>
			<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-594" type="subject">Policy</term> of <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004295">Bulgarian Government</orgName> upon its self-created <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-351" type="subject">Jewish problem</term> has in the last few days clearly
				become directed towards <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">elimination</term> of the
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jewish population</term>. In closed meeting of
				government’s staunch parliamentary supporters Minister <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000132"
					>Gabrovski</persName> reportedly stated government had in resisting pressure to declare <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080" type="subject">war</term> on <ref
					target="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soviet_Union">Russia</ref> accepted <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">German</term> pressure to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">liquidate</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-872" type="subject">Jewish communities</term>.</p>
			<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">Liquidation</term> is now being ruthlessly carried
				out in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1031" type="subject">annexed territories</term> where <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jewish</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1031" type="subject">deportees</term> are shipped in open freight cars
				to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">concentration camps</term>. Each <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1031" type="subject">deportee</term> is <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-660" type="subject">stripped his valuables</term> and warm clothing. The
				daily food ration is 200 grams of bread. [...] <pb n="2" facs="R 87-11 17 (39)"/> In <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/732800/republic-of-bulgaria.html">Bulgaria</placeName> proper the authorities are acting more
				temperately where the sensibilities <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-637" type="subject">non-Jewish
					Bulgarians</term> are involved. Preparations made for <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1031"
					type="subject">deportation</term> to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName> of
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jews</term> from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/729730/kyustendil.html">Kyustendil</placeName>, <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/728193/plovdiv.html">Plovdiv</placeName>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/725578/yambol.html"
					>Yambol</placeName>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/732770/burgas.html">Burgas</placeName> and other towns of <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/732800/republic-of-bulgaria.html">Bulgaria</placeName> proper were suspended after strong protests by
				prominent <term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_bulgarians">Bulgarians</term> in these towns supported by the Archbishops of <ref
					target="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stefan_I_of_Bulgaria">Sofia</ref> and <ref
					target="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cyril_of_Bulgaria"
				>Plovdiv</ref>.<?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?></p>
